	abstract = {For effective radiative forcing (ERF) to be an ideal metric for comparing the strength of different climate drivers (such as CO
              2
              and aerosols), the ratio of radiative forcing to global-mean temperature change must be the same for each driver. Typically, this ratio is divided by the same ratio for CO
              2
              and termed efficacy. Previously it has been shown that efficacy is close to unity in abrupt perturbation experiments for a range of climate drivers, but efficacy with respect to CO
